caption: Sweet

I've been meaning to come to Thai Farm kitchen for the longest time but the pandemic happened and everything changed. Now that i have a change to try it out. I am glad i did although this are not back to normal you do have the options of dining in or sitting outside. Overall i must say it was quiet the service was great food was absolutely delicious although my entree was a bit too spicy but i did survive . i will be back.
Wow! SO DELICIOUS! Their fries egg is the best ever! 🍳
Always the best Thai I can find in NYC!!! Tried the green papaya, avocado sald for first time, delicious!!!
Cozy, authentic and with good service. I highly recommend it and will likely be back soon. The Pad See Ew is the best I’ve had in all of NYC. Must try!

It's a great Thai restaurant to go with family or friends. Let the waitress know how much spicy do you like for the food, they can adjust for you the spiciness level that you like. This restaurant got the best sticky rice dessert!!! Sweet taste with coconut milk sauce on it. MUST TRY!!
Food was great. Service was fantastic. Ive been searching for Thai food for some time in the area and finally found it. Quality is A1.

My wife and I had a great time at this restaurant! The seafood paella we shared was very good. The show is very good as well. I recommend this restaurant for the food, the atmosphere, and the entertainment show. We thoroughly enjoyed our meal and would go back in a heartbeat. We will definitely come back!

I remembered first eating here two years ago and being mesmerized by the quality of their food. I'm glad they still kept the same awesome ambience and left a great impression.  Staff was very courteous, wearing masks at all times, giving helpful suggestions. Very cute decor featuring local designs. Definitely brings me back to traveling in Chiang Mai. They respected covid guidelines with limited seating, about 3-4 tables a good distance apart. All tables had hand sanitizers and were properly cleaned by staff in between.  Their food. Mouth watering delicious! Honestly, we couldn't decide on one thing and over ordered by getting 3-4 dishes. Everything was a homerun! Authentic flavors. -Thai iced tea. -Thai farm kitchen Pad Thai with a side of shrimp and calamari. -Massaman look Kae. That coconut sauce was delicious. Lamb was fall off the bone. -Pad Krapow. Ground pork with rice topped with fried egg. Really really good. We ordered another to go!  Left full and satisfied. Big portions, guaranteed leftovers. Will continue to support this place!

Placed an online order through their own website and received a confirmation email that it will take 90 minutes.  I live about half a mile away, I can pick it up myself and finish eating before a 90 minute delivery.  I called to cancel it right away (unfortunately, you don't get a delivery time until after an order is placed) and they assured me that it will only take 50 minutes max.  Of course the time flies by and after not receiving anything, I call over an hour later and if course they gave me story that it is on its way.  Now, they claim they can't cancel it and made it seem like I'm causing them a major disservice ( it's already an hour and twenty minutes and I have no food).  No apologies.  They can't take the responsibility to call someone that they are running late or anything.  I wish I could give them no stars.
Love the food, quick delivery. Definitely worth the price
Can it be eaten in the restaurant now?
Don’t skip on the Koay Tiaw Tom Yum 🤤 it was probably one of the best things I’ve had. Def looking forward to trying more of the menu items and dining there!
I like it

I've been searching for a while for a good Thai restaurant in Brooklyn and I finally found it! Thai Farm Kitchen was so tasty! Both of the dishes we got were plentiful, well-balanced, and very fresh. The iced tea with milk was perfect... I find a lot of places put a ton of sugar in it which makes it undrinkable, but here it was just right, I could drink 3 of them in a row they were so amazing. The lemon tea was also very refreshing. I LOVE the many vegan options and how committed they seem to the community. My boyfriend and I laugh and say we're officially farm people now. Their restaurant looks beautiful and exciting, I really want to experience their food on location. Definitely going to order from here again (from their website so they get the profit instead of the leeching delivery websites) and I look forward to going to Thai Farm Kitchen in person!
Loved the food and the tea.  Great service all around.
Best thai in the neighborhood by far
Perfect service, very flavorful food, comfortable outdoor seating. Underpriced for what it is, a must try in the neighborhood.

The food  quality is excellent making this place a standout among many bad-to-mediocre Thai places in the area. Even though prices here are Manhattan level, they are perpetually busy and will think of nothing to put you on 15 minutes hold on the phone and manage to actively ignore you when inside despite the tiny size of the restaurant. This is not through the fault of their own - this area is in desperate need of higher quality food, and Thai Farm Kitchen fills the small percentage of the demand. Be prepared to wait. But it will be worth it. And the owner is a kind man with genuine integrity.
New local favorite! The shrimp rolls, panang curry, fried catfish 👍

I celebrated my nomination last night in this great restaurant. happy to tell that we passed a tremendous evening and the venue was no doubt one of the reasons for this strong evening. The stuff  cooperated in a sweet way, the meals were tasty and my friends were so  cheerful. We shall absolutely visit again for more celebrations. thanks very much.
Good fod but the staff are not.

I ordered Thai Farm through delivery dot com and had the pad see ew with chicken. It arrived quickly and was piping hot (almost too hot which was great). The chicken was delicious, it wasn't overly sauced and it's just a perfect little dish for a rainy day. I also had chicken panang curry which was ABSOLUTELY DELICIOUS! I rationed it out over four meals since it was so good!

Thoroughly magnificent. Everything I've ever gotten here is fantastic, which is cool because it gives me the confidence to try everything on the menu! The food is thoughtfully and freshly prepared, never too greasy/salty/sweet, and flavors are excellent. As if that's not enough, the staff are deeply professional and kind, and this place has been a great neighbor and partner in the community during COVID, sending meals to people in need. A high-quality menu and a high-integrity establishment deserving of your business.

Fine place for delicious Thai food. I love eating here. I've had nothing but pleasant experiences here and plan to keep coming back. It has an awesome atmosphere. Food is like a restaurant in Louisville I loved.
A fav place for Thai food. Do not leave if it's busy, it is worth it. Looking forward to returning with my relatives. The bill was average for the menu.
Great food as expected! Love, love the Tom Yum Noodle dish(Y28)! Highly recommended especially for hot and spicy food lovers. It's just addictive, you won't be able to stop eating it.
I eat in this spot a lot since I work nearby. I like how the service is always good and they keep the spot well kept at all times. Prices are reasonable and they serve generous portions.

Really great food. I have been many times and always enjoyed. I did order the masaman curry in April and it had a strange flavor to it but just might be my preference. My usual order is the Penang curry with extra shrimp and it’s a solid choice. My friend loves the fried catfish dish but would wait thill they are open for sit down again as I don’t see that traveling well.
I certainly enjoyed their dishes and customer service, good area very close to my apartment. The workers are always very friendly. Will visit here again.
Awesome and flavorful food, I loved the vibes the place has, and the cashiers were friendly. I will surely visit here again.
Horrible food, ordered delivery.

Went to thai farm kitchen today after a long quarantine stint for some takeout. Let me tell you that these people know how to respect a business and support a community. They are giving free meals to the less fortunate during this hard time in the community which honestly doesn't surprise me these people are just that humble and loving. All employees are in masks and gloves with a plastic divider and table to pass food along with some hand sanitizer on the table aswell. No one in there was not in a mask or gloves including the chefs. These businesses support us when we're up and I have to say how pleased I was to support them when they're down and feel as comfortable as I did leaving because naturally we're all nervous. I love this place in general but have an added respect after seeing their community initiative and thankfulness for my business during this tough time.  Food is always top notch I don't even need to comment. It's always on point it's the best thai in the area and I drive 20 minutes for it no lies. I don't write reviews on google but heavily rely on them. I just finished my meal and absolutely needed to review. Thanks!

They got rid of the lunch special on such a time where people who don’t have jobs need it the most???? People can’t even afford the regular price of this restaurant due to how expensive this place is... can’t believe they’re  not offering their lunch special ... most people cant even afford since lunch special was helpful lmao Sorry not buying from here again

My new favorite Thai place in the neighborhood! Their dishes are so unique, the Thai farm pad Thai is a must.  It was our first time ordering and we had a question regarding delivery— I couldn’t get through on their phone line, so I sent them an email instead and the owner called me right away. Great service and I absolutely recommend :)
This place provides excellent service and delightful food. The best restaurant in the city. The food and drinks arrived rapidly and the rates were economical. Recommended.
Not bad but very tiny. Good is not bad but overpriced
Everything is delicious. Especially the curry puffs.

Wow what an experience this place is! You must go here if you want a delicious, carefully crafted plate of food. The ingredients are the freshest possible and you can taste it on every bite. Their soups and currys are very good and also the Thai Fried Rice. Try the butterfly pea tea and you won't be disappointed. Their customer service is exceptional and the prices are good. The restaurant is cozy and comfortable, however small, we didn't have to wait but I can see it being very crowded on the weekends.
Popular local thai place.  Very good service.  The food was great. It's a tight location and crowded. Definitely want to call ahead of time if you plan on visiting.
My kid loves the food here and so do I.
Excellent food. A step above your normal Thai fare
The place is clean and wonderful to eat and food is great
This was my first visit cause it was recommended by my friend. The food and service were great. Pretty authentic and I will return another visit.
Excellent
SO GOOD, cannot wait to go back! Great service, great menu, reasonable prices!
Great service and better food
Amazing authentic Thai food.
Food was so great and service was quite good .  Venue is a bit cramped but they make it work and somehow adds to ambience.
After trying every Thai restaurant in the neighborhood, I’d say this is my favorite.
Our party of four went for the first time today and it was great. Food was delicious and the staff was super friendly. Definitely will be coming back.

they consistently serve excellent food and their service is as excellent as the food! we tried different dishes over time and they were all amazing! They also offer delivery that you can use when you don’t feel like going out!

I absolutely love this restaurant.  The food is always amazing and the service is gracious, warm and competent.  Tonight we had a long wait since a large party decided to hang out.  But the owners made this a gentle experience, keeping us comfortable, offering us tea on the house, and then coming over to check in on us.  So warm: like being in a good friend's home--one who can really cook!

Came here not too long ago and I wasn’t sure what to expect which made the experience even better. The food is delicious. My favorite Thai place. I tried a few of their dishes since and haven’t been disappointed. Highly recommend this spot

Been here a few times and literally everything we’ve tried has been amazing. Great noodles, small dishes, large plates, soups everything! It’s a small place that fills up quick. They charge less if you pay cash FYI.
Great food, nice owners.
Amazing food and service at this little gem!!
Very good tasty food next time I'll ask for less spicy
Clean food well prepared and excellently presented
Excellent fresh Thai specialty foods and drinks. Great lunch special. Already beloved in our neighborhood 👌
Decent place.
The pad see ew was a little dry and tasteless compared to other Thai restaurants I’ve ordered from.
Great 12.99 weekday lunch set.
Very good but not the best in town

Everything was fresh, flavorful, and delicious. There's an extensive menu of authentic Thai dishes which initially left me thinking that we'd get pretty ordinary food. Nothing could be further from the truth. Everything we ordered came beautifully presented and imaginatively concieved in a way unique to this restaurant. I don't live nearby and it was bad planning that landed us here looking for a place to eat, but our lunch, at least,  was serendipitously amazing.
Amazing and complex flavors, high quality ingredients. Great service and affordable prices. Highly recommended. Loved the dry rub ribs appetizer and the garlic shrimp are exceptional
I like the food and Service is good
The food was very good and well presented. The service was above average and it had a good crowd.
The lunch special here is so good and such a great deal.
Delivery takes way too long.  I live a block away and our dinner took over an two hours.
Delicious food served by friendly folks. If you're not one who enjoys hot (spicy) food, pay attention to the "peppers" on the menu. One pepper means the food is hot.
Top Thai restaurant in my book. Delicious food! Fantastic experience... warm welcoming and consistent. Thank you guys for putting love in your food and your service.

We love our thai food and have been to many restaurants in this neighborhood and all over the city, but this was still a very pleasant surprise. Very authentic (food is served on a plate with a banana leaf) and delicious. Staff is extremely friendly and the owner is very welcoming and sweet. This is definitely our top choice now ☺

excellent food, really enjoyed it. Only taking a star away because they put in a load of plastic cutlery. Why when food is being delivered to people's homes do they put it in. Should only be when it is asked for
This Thai Farm Kitchen restaurant serves the most delicious and authentic Thai food in Buffalo. The service is also amazing. Definitely my new favorite Thai spot.....
Extremely good service. Very delicious food. Is a must visit place. Highly recommend the green curry chicken, fried chicken wing with sticky rice, and the mango rice dessert. Yum..

This restaurant is amazing! The owners and servers are incredibly friendly, the restaurant feels warm and inviting, and the food is straight-up incredible. Everything is fresh, the dishes are delicious, and we always leave satisfied. Highly recommend!

My favorite authentic Thai Restaurant in the Borough. The spring rolls, chicken laab, and hot + sour noodle soup 🍜 are incredible. The service is warm, friendly, and efficient. It’s worth traveling an hour on the train for.
The food was absolutely delicious!!!! Try everything!

The Food and Service is superb. Very happy to know this place. Their attachment to details on food and experience will keep them making a lot People very happy. The drunken noodles where amazing. The coconut rice had a special color and aroma was great. The soup was perfect. And the creamy clean taste of the shrimp coconut curry will make me comeback millions times more to eat it again. The decor make u feel at home same with the flavor of the food. This place everybody in the word should try many times if they are hardcore Thai food fans. 👍👍👍👍. Thanks.
The best Thai, everything I've had is amazing, all organic
Excellent food and very good service.  I recommend it!
This place just cares.  The organic food was excellent and their attention to detail was inspiring. I watched the manager correct the exact placement of the place mats and coach the wait staff.
Polite and delicious food!
The best Thai in the history of church ave! Superior quality and super delicious

Best authentic Thai place in Brooklyn! It’s a family owned restaurant that uses fresh and organic ingredients. They have vegan options and are flexible when it comes to making substitutes. The food is delicious! The waiter was attentive and was really great about answering all our questions. Its definitely a smaller restaurant so if you have a big group, call ahead so they can be prepared with the table arrangement!
Well decorate place, food is delicious, get 5% discount if pay by cash.
The food and the room are simple and delicious. The staff is courteous and attendive.
Excellent Thai food in a tiny place.

We rolled the dice and went here for lunch on a rainy weekday...our gamble paid off: lovely atmosphere, excellent service and good to fabulous fare. They emphasize the healthy side here with more fresh and crisp vegetables than at other Thai restaurants we've been to. The pork laab appetizer is very tasty and has a bit of a kick. Pad Thai was really good. The only negative was that the Panang curry could have been richer and spicier,  theirs was a bit watery. Making up for it though was the delicious dessert of taro, coconut and pumpkin. Best of all was their spectacularly good ice coffee with milk: I want a glass every morning for the rest of my life!

Really homey and delicious place for Thai food in the area. Got a Thai Iced Tea and got a sweet surprise. Would definitely recommend getting the seafood stuffed coconut curry. Super delicious and enough to share between two people!

Hands down, the best Thai food in Brooklyn. The food is absolutely delicious and they run the extra mile to serve the dishes in a beautiful way. The staff is welcoming and friendly. I highly recommend it.
Very tasty thai food with rich flavour!

The best thing to happen to Church Ave in Kensington in years. Every dish is a revelation and will have you rethinking Thai food. The fact that people come from the city to done here isn't for nothing. It's that good.
Great place to be closed at 4pm.
This is the real deal! Excellent meal plus BYOB. Every dish was incredible.
We ordered from here before. Pretty good and it reminds me of East Village Thai restaurant which has been permanently closed this year.
The serving size is not to my satisfaction considering the price of a meal there.

Cute place. This neighborhood deserves something like this. I lived here for many years before moving and if this was here when I was, I would have earned the title of most frequent customer.  Food is fresh and authentic. Not too many seats but honestly who cares.  Price is a touch on the high side but I'm sure the neighborhood is changing and is driving those prices. I have no issues with it personally, especially given the organic farm to table approach.  I will be back to sample more of the menu.

I absolutely loved this place. The service was great and the food was delicious. I was the only one in our party who liked spicy food, so the owner helped me with the special seasonings to make it hotter just for me. I especially liked the chicken coconut soup and the drunken noodles dish with shrimp.

Been here for over 5 times and have tried different dishes they offer. Everything I have tried tastes more than delicious, and they are authentic, feeling as if I were in Thailand. All produce is organic and straight from farms, so it is fresh and tasty. Service is great too and I love coming back whenever I want Thai food.
Great food and fast service
Very good addition to the area

Five stars for the service and four and a half star for the food. It's quiet good in my opinion but not great. However you'll definitely enjoy your time at this place. The $12.95 deal is great for the price.
Really tasty Thai food. Fresh and fast. Great prices.
Awesome
Fresh food.

Food was great but service was slow, especially given that we were one of only two tables in the entire restaurant. We weren’t even offered water until I finally was able to flag someone down for it. Weekday lunch specials look like a good deal.
Excellent food. Snall place so be prepared to wait if you go at peak times. But the wait is worth it.
The lunch special is delicious and such a deal!
Yummy
Lovely tasty beautiful food in a chill place at fair prices  Plating is beautiful Service is kind and attentive Place is clean and comfy  Just come  And eat the friend fish!!!

Very attentive service with lots of smiles from everyone who worked there, which made us feel very welcomed. The food was Tasty with lots of dishes that contained lots Of fresh vegetables, special sauces and spices, some with different levels of heat Other with no heat .Our server helped us choose the level of heat we desired. The chicken meatballs soup was so Delicious packed with chunks of fresh veggies, the vegetarian dumplings was the best  I have had , the shrimp &squid with salty egg was so tender & had a really delicious red curry sauce. I will definitely return, have my eyes on The steamed whole fish, the duck & lamb Shank. Mmmmmm

We are lucky enough to live in this area close to 3 other Thai food and many many more variety of crusine. This place stands out in term of quality, service and ambiance.  I was amazed how the decoration in this place. Before we entered, their front door stands out so clearly from the neighbors. With two Golden dragons outside, you feel like transported to an other place. In side you will see the open kitchen and smell the food being made. It is lunch hour on a Sunday but pretty empty. I recommend the window table. This is perfect for a date and not for more than 4 people.  With real fork and spoon, I felt like having fine dining here. I actually like their utensil better. Service is really good. Lemon water and menu given to us right after we settle down. There is your five star service.  The best part is the food. I was a bit up sad that their lunch special only apply for weekday. I kinda want to try everything here but we got papaya salad and green curry. Food is 100% and presentation is even better.  Definitely do trek out here for a try.
Food was delicious and fresh. They pay attention to small details and you can tell by how well everything is prepared.

The atmosphere is lovely. Beautiful,  nice & cozy.  Staff are friendly & warm.  I've tried Thai Farm Kitchen three times, trying to give them a chance to wow me with their cuisine.  But no, the food is terrible , & I love Thai food. The dishes don't even look appetizing.

Fantastically authentic Thai food and great service. It's very popular so be prepared to wait. Decide what you want to order while waiting for your table so when you sit down, you are that much closer to enjoying the amazing food!
The food is Authentic is tasty.  Everything is great about this restaurant.

4.5 stars. It's got everything you'd expect from a Thai restaurant - tasty and flavorful food, pleasant and helpful service, clean dining area. The sticky rice was a little too sticky and the place was packed during our visit, so the noise level was a bit intolerable at times. We paid $44 (inclusive of tips) for two mains, an appetizer, and a drink.  Great place overall and definitely a nice addition to the neighborhood.
Great tasting food with excellent service and warm ambiance, all at a reasonable price.
One of the best restaurants on Church Ave

Pretty good Thai place! The restaurant is kind of unassuming from the outside but it is pretty well decorated on the inside. It felt very welcoming.  The food was pretty tasty and the portions were fair. I got the Pad Krapow which consisted of rice with stir fried ground pork (also available with chicken) and a perfectly fried egg. It was slightly spicy but not overly so, just overall a great dish. I got the hot tea which was really flavorful.  Service is great and everyone was very friendly. Prices are slightly high but I would say cheaper than comparable Thai restaurants. I would definitely say this is a two dollar sign place rather than one dollar sign as Google Maps shows.
Lucky to have this gem in my neighborhood. Authentic flavors. My only criticism is that they  should play Thai music, it would round out the whole food experience. I will be returning..
We live in the neighborhood and eat here regularly.  Food is outstanding and the ownership could not be any friendlier.  I highly recommend.
This place is straight up so delicious, they’re super kind and everything we had was on point. 100 percent going back, and then again, then again.

Just dined here last night. Food and service is great! I had the deep fried whole branzino.  The fish was fried to perfection and was very flavorful. The owners/staff are so friendly and accommodating. The only thing is that this place is a bit small and can't accommodate large crowds. So there is a wait time. Also, they don't serve alchohol, but the Iced Thai Lemon Tea was good....a tad sweet, but good. Will definitely come back here again to try something else or get the food to go as they do takeout service as well.
Everyone is friendly in there and food was delicious. They need better ventilation since its an open kitchen. But Will definitely return to try other dishes.
The REAL DEAL. After today’s glowing NYTimes review though the cat is out of the bag. May honest home cooking and hard work always be celebrated. Mazel tov

My Thai cravings usually take me to another local place (Am Thai), but I've been meaning to check this place out with the marvelous Yelp reviews. I came with high expectations and wasn't let down!  The waitress was friendly and the owner (I think) came to check up on me as well which was nice. My service was quick! I my Thai ice tea came out quickly followed shortly by my Tom yum soup. My ice tea was great and my soup was flavorful (although I wish it had a bit more spice).  The menu here isn't typically what you would find in an American Thai restaurant, most of the menu was actually quite foreign to me, I decided to try outside my comfort zone. I don't usually like Thai curries because of the overwhelming taste of coconut but I thought my entree was phenomenal (also beautifully presented) , I ordered the green curry with chicken and there was a good balance of cocunut and the other flavors. I actually gulfed down the remaining curry like soup after finishing the chicken with white rice.  To sum it up. In my experience good food and service. Price for dinner felt a little steep around $30 for one person. I'll be back to try some other things regardless though.
Fantastic place. Interior, food, the staff, everything.
Fresh and beautifully seasoned. I will be back many times.

Wow- so happy to have stumbled upon this amazing restaurant. Farm to table thai food done right. The owners are very friendly and everything we ordered was fantastic. They don't serve liquor but if you bring some wine they will gladly open it for you. We can't wait to go back and take all our friends. They will accommodate if you are vegetarian/vegan.
Delicious authentic food. Friendly welcoming  people make you feel like at home.. Very busy and long wait but worth every minute.

Overall awful experience. Not only was the food bland and ice cold, but the Pad Thai gave me a severe case of food poisoning. Never visit this place. And besides, why not boycott the infamous military junta of not-even-regionally important Thailand? I'd much rather stick to my local Kensington and much less overpriced Halal Hui Chinese eatery. Much less gentrifying too. Two energetic thumbs DOWN!
This place is great and right next door to my work place. The food is great too.
True authenticity in the taste, you have to try to believe. Wonderful staff!there desert is out of this world!

Love this place! Staff/owners are extremely friendly and accommodating. Decor is very warm and chill (much better than dark, dreary atmosphere of the previous business in that location) and most of all food is great! Fresh and delicious. Bring a bottle of wine to pair with your meal.
This is a great restaurant with a strong commitment to sustainability.

There are already 4-5 Thai restaurants in this neighborhood, most of them aren't good. I love Thai food so I had high hopes for this place when it 1st opened. Unfortunately, we now have a new contender for worse Thai restaurant in the neighborhood.

First I just want to say Thank You for serving AUTHENTIC Thai food and not westernized version, because I’m sick and tired of them. I just chowed down my Pla Tod, and Som Tum. Let me just say it is one of the best Som Tum I’ve had in a restaurant in the west. And the sauce that came with my Pla Tod was just too delicious! The owner and the staff are super friendly. I will definitely be back, welcome to the Neighborhood!

My brother and sister-in-law took me to Thai Farm Kitchen because they know I love authentic Thai food made with fresh ingredients and undiluted flavors.  The bolder, the better.  They use very fresh ingredients and the flavors are vibrant and bold, one of the closest in flavor to the food we had in Bangkok when we visited many years ago.  No goopy, sweet flavors.  The owner, Jess, came over and greeted us and was very friendly, sharing stories of his life in Thailand as a farmer/restaurateur and educator in agricultural studies.  It is obvious he has a passion for real Thai food culture and wants to share it with his customers.  Hope Thai Farm Kitchen is around for a long time.  Good luck, Jess!

Loved restaurant that support organic and local farmer. The taste of the dishes were authentic. Disliked a lot of the Thai restaurant altering the taste to suit the western culture. The dishes here are not salty. If you are not fan of spicy food or can't take too hot. Definitely go for mild.

This is a new Thai restaurant in the area. Although there are other Thai restaurants just within a few blocks, no other place beats the food and service of this restaurant. Service is impeccable, and the dishes are prepared with fresh ingredients. Menu selection is just large enough not to overwhelm you with numerous choices. The space is not very large so I would recommend it for a nice romantic dinner but not for large parties.

caption: Love love love the food, real classic Thai. The owner Jess and Elizabeth are such a warm host!

Great local family-run Thai restaurant serving excellent Thai food. The owner, Jess, and his family were incredibly friendly and the lunch special was delicious and great value for money. Happy to welcome his family to the neighborhood. I’ll definitely be back soon.
